      <ecm_name><![CDATA[Weather Compensation for heating and cooling]]></ecm_name>
      <description><![CDATA[This control ECM enables to implement optimized control laws to determine the flow temperature of hot water loops accounting for variations of the outdoor temperature. ]]></description>
    </level>
  </ecm_catalogue>
  <component_catalogue>
    <level id="7">
      <application><![CDATA[The ECM can be applied to any hot water loop and requires to define a linear relationship between measured outdoor temperature and water flow temperature set-point.]]></application>
      <functional_unit><![CDATA[[null]]]></functional_unit>
      <advantages><![CDATA[The weather compensated control enables to tune the level of energy delivered to the building depending on environmental conditions such that relevant comfort DPIs can be better optimized along with energy and economic DPIs.]]></advantages>
      <disadvantages><![CDATA[The ECM may need tuning during commissioning  such that the best performances are achieved.]]></disadvantages>
      <links_to_barriers><![CDATA[This control ECM implementation requires hardware (such as timer, smart thermostat or BMS) and measurement system (temperature sensers) ]]></links_to_barriers>
      <links_to_targets><![CDATA[[null]]]></links_to_targets>
